    • Class ixa.kaflib.Term extends IReferable implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • tid

          String tid
          Term's ID (required)

        • type

          String type
          Type of the term (optional). Currently, 2 values are possible: open and close.

        • lemma

          String lemma
          Lemma of the term (optional)

        • pos

          String pos
          Part of speech (optional). Possible values are: - common noun (N) - proper noun (R) - adjective (G) - verb (V) - preposition (P) - adverb (A) - conjunction (C) - determiner (D) - other (O)

        • morphofeat

          String morphofeat
          Morphosyntactic feature encoded as a single attribute (optional)

        • termcase

          String termcase
          Declension case of the term (optional)

        • sentiment

          Term.Sentiment sentiment
          Sentiment features (optional)

        • components

          List<E> components
          If it's a compound term, it's components (optional)

        • head

          Term head
          Head component (optional)

        • span

          Span<T> span
          Target elements are used to refer to the target word. If the term is a multiword, multiple target elements are used. (required)

        • externalReferences

          List<E> externalReferences
          ExternalReferences are used to associate terms to external lexical or semantic resources, such as elements of a Knowledge base: semantic lexicon (like WordNet) or an ontology (optional)

        • isComponent

          boolean isComponent

        • compound

          Term compound

        • supersenseTag

          String supersenseTag

        • wordnetSense

          String wordnetSense

        • bbnTag

          String bbnTag

        • upos

          String upos

        • features

          Map<K,V> features

    • Class ixa.kaflib.Term.Sentiment extends Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • resource

          String resource
          Identifier and reference to an external sentiment resource (optional)

        • polarity

          String polarity
          Refers to the property of a word to express positive, negative or no sentiment (optional). These values are possible: - Positive - Negative - Neutral - Or numerical value on a numerical scale

        • strength

          String strength
          Refers to the strength of the polarity (optional). These values are possible: - Weak - Average - Strong - Or Numerical value

        • subjectivity

          String subjectivity
          Refers to the property of a words to express an opionion (or not) (optional). - Subjective/Objective - Factual/opinionated

        • sentimentSemanticType

          String sentimentSemanticType
          Refers to a sentiment-related semantic type (optional): - Aesthetics_evaluation - Moral_judgment - Emotion - etc

        • sentimentModifier

          String sentimentModifier
          Refers to words which modify the polarity of another word (optional): - Intensifier/weakener polarity shifter

        • sentimentMarker

          String sentimentMarker
          Refers to words which themselves do not carry polarity, but are kind of vehicles of it (optional): - Find, think, in my opinion, according to...

        • sentimentProductFeature

          String sentimentProductFeature
          Refers to a domain; mainly used in feature-based sentiment analysis (optional): - Values are related to specific domain. For the tourist domain, for example, staff, cleanliness, beds, bathroom, transportation, location, etc...
